{{Orphan|date=December 2008}}

'''Programming Metadata Communications Protocol''' (PMCP) is an [[open-source]], device-independent [[eXtensible Markup Language]] (XML) [[XML Schema|schema]] developed and published by the [[Advanced Television Systems Committee]] (ATSC) that is used to communicate data elements needed to create PSIP and MPEG-2 PSI within a transmission facility and to communicate the data between and among transmission facilities and other points.<ref>{{cite web
|url=http://www.tvtechnology.com/features/atsc/f_jw_atsc_update-01.07.04.shtml|title=TVTechnology - ATSC Update
|publisher=www.tvtechnology.com|accessdate=2008-08-09|last=|first=}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.atsc.org/news_information/papers/2004/Implementing_Closed_Captioning.pdf|title=Implementing_Closed_Captioning.pdf (application/pdf Object)|publisher=www.atsc.org|accessdate=2008-08-09|last=|first=}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref>

